ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: Well worth taking, great survey course for methods.
Great class if you want to do applied math or engineering.
It covers the material well and I would recommend it to another student interested in the subject or to someone who would find it useful in research.

I would summarize it as "the problems that arise in mathematics when you can't assume infinitesimal accuracy". I would recommend it to other students if only to have them experience the character that is Prof. Rockhlin.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: Helps a lot for programming and applied math.
It introduced me to methods that I did not know before and taught me when to use the various methods.
It will help me avoid numerical mistakes and recheck my assumptions when conducting research. It also improved my coding skills.
